data.name: graphmap

evidence: README mentions binaries/installers: "Run ```sudo make install``` to install the graphmap binary to ```/usr/bin```."
Quick start shows cloning and building an executable tool: `git clone https://github.com/isovic/graphmap.git` then `make` and run `./bin/Linux-x64/graphmap align ...`

Described as a mapper/overlapper users run for alignment and assembly tasks: `GraphMap is a novel mapper targeted at aligning long, error-prone third-generation sequencing data.` and `./graphmap align ...` usage examples.
